data.chText: 食物
生的；未烹制的；未煮的
生肉
这些鱼常常生吃。
data.enText: These fish are often eaten raw.

data.chText: 材料
未经加工的；自然状态的
data.enText: in its natural state; not yet changed, used or made into sth else

data.chText: 原糖
信息
未经处理的；未经分析的；原始的
data.enText: not yet organized into a form in which it can be easily used or understood

data.chText: 这些资料只是原始数据，还需要进一步进行分析。
data.enText: This information is only raw data and will need further analysis.

data.chText: 情感；品质
未经训练的；粗犷的
data.enText: powerful and natural; not controlled or trained

data.chText: 充满豪放情感的歌曲
他起家时只有天生的才能和决心。
data.enText: He started with nothing but raw talent and determination.

data.chText: 身体部位
红肿疼痛的；皮肤破损的；擦伤的
data.enText: red and painful because the skin has been damaged

data.chText: 她的双脚被鞋子磨破了好几块皮。
data.enText: There were raw patches on her feet where the shoes had rubbed.

data.chText: 人
工作生疏的；不熟练的；无经验的
data.enText: new to a job or an activity and therefore without experience or skill

data.chText: 没有经验的新手
未经训练的新兵
data.enText: raw recruits (= for example, in the army)

data.chText: 天气
寒冷的；严寒的
寒冷的北风
那是一个寒冷潮湿的冬天。
data.enText: It had been a wet raw winter.

data.chText: 描述
真实的；反映真实情况的
工人阶级生活的真实写照
data.enText: a raw portrayal of working-class life

data.chText: 粗鲁的语言
data.enText: raw language (= containing many sexual details)

data.chText: 不公平的待遇；不公正的对待
data.enText: the fact of sb being treated unfairly

data.chText: 年纪大的工人经常受到不公正的对待。
data.enText: Older workers often get a raw deal.

data.chText: 触到某人的痛处；揭某人的疮疤
data.enText: to upset sb by reminding them of sth they are particularly sensitive about

data.chText: 质朴的；不加掩饰的
data.enText: in a way that does not hide the unpleasant aspects of sth

data.chText: 他花了几个月时间走街串巷，体验真实的生活。
data.enText: He spent a couple of months on the streets to experience life in the raw.

data.chText: 赤条条；赤身裸体；一丝不挂
以上各词均指使人肉体上疼痛的。
data.enText: These words all describe sth that causes you physical pain.

data.chText: 指使人肉体上疼痛的。
painful可用于身体部位、疾病、受伤、治疗或死亡等：
data.enText: Painful can describe a part of the body, illness, injury, treatment or death.

data.chText: 你的膝盖还疼吗？
一次又一次令人痛苦的注射
缓慢而痛苦的死亡
指（身体部位）发炎疼痛的、肌肉酸痛的：
data.enText: (of a part of the body) painful and often red, especially because of infection or because a muscle has been used too much

data.chText: 咽喉疼
他们走了几小时的路把脚都走疼了。
data.enText: Their feet were sore after hours of walking.

data.chText: 指（身体部位）红肿疼痛、破损、擦伤：
data.enText: (of a part of the body) red and painful, for example because of an infection or because the skin has been damaged

data.chText: 她脚上的皮磨破了。
data.enText: The skin on her feet had been rubbed raw.

data.chText: 指极痛苦、极苦恼。
excruciating可用于情感、待遇或死亡，而非身体部位：
data.enText: Excruciating can describe feelings, treatments or death but not parts of the body.

data.chText: 指火辣辣的痛、发烫：
data.enText: painful and giving a feeling of being very hot

data.chText: 她感到咽喉火辣辣的疼。
data.enText: She felt a burning sensation in her throat.

ex.chText: 这是一种自然现象，几乎每个世纪都要发生一次。
ex.enText: This is a natural phenomenon that happens about once a century.

ex.chText: 她做饭只用纯天然的佐料。
ex.enText: She cooks with natural ingredients only.

synonyms.bx: 指存在或发生于自然界的，含非人力所为之意，也指食物没有添加其他成分的。

ex.chText: 汽油是从原油中提炼出来的。
ex.enText: Gasoline is made from crude oil.

ex.chText: 他们从马来西亚进口生胶。
ex.enText: They imported crude rubber from Malaysia.

synonyms.bx: 主要指石油、橡胶等未经化学加工、尚处于自然状态的，只作定语。

ex.chText: 这家工厂经常原料不足。
ex.enText: The factory is in frequent scarcity of raw materials.

ex.chText: 他也用自己的船从美国进口原棉。
ex.enText: He also imported raw cotton from America in his own ships.

synonyms.bx: 指物质未经加工、依然处于自然状态的。

ex.chText: 未提炼的猪油/原糖/未精制的糖浆

synonyms.bx: 指物质处于天然或未经精炼状态的，通常含有其他杂质。

synonym.guide: 导航词义：自然的，天然的

data.chText: 不公平的待遇；不公正的对待
data.enText: the fact of sb being treated unfairly

data.chText: 年纪大的工人经常受到不公正的对待。
data.enText: Older workers often get a raw deal.

data.chText: 触到某人的痛处；揭某人的疮疤
data.enText: to upset sb by reminding them of sth they are particularly sensitive about

data.chText: 质朴的；不加掩饰的
data.enText: in a way that does not hide the unpleasant aspects of sth

data.chText: 他花了几个月时间走街串巷，体验真实的生活。
data.enText: He spent a couple of months on the streets to experience life in the raw.

data.chText: 赤条条；赤身裸体；一丝不挂
触及要害；触动痛处
data.enText: to mention a subject that makes sb feel angry, upset, embarrassed, etc.

data.chText: 你谈起他的第一个妻子，这就触到了他的痛处。
data.enText: You touched a raw nerve when you mentioned his first wife.

tr: not processed or subjected to analysis
not treated with heat to prepare it for eating

example: the new men were eager to fight
received raw treatment from his friends
bleak winds of the North Atlantic

tr: having the surface exposed and painful
devoid of elaboration or diminution or concealment
example: you may kill someone someday with your raw power
the tender spot on his jaw

value.def: Raw materials or substances are in their natural state before being processed or used in manufacturing.

example.ex: We import raw materials and energy and export mainly industrial products.
example.tran: 我们进口原材料和能源，主要出口工业产品。

example.ex: ...two ships carrying raw sugar from Cuba.
example.tran: 两艘来自古巴装有粗糖的船

value.tran: 未经加工的;天然状态的

value.def: Raw food is food that is eaten uncooked, that has not yet been cooked, or that has not been cooked enough.

example.ex: ...a popular dish made of raw fish...
example.tran: 受欢迎的生鱼菜肴

example.ex: This versatile vegetable can be eaten raw or cooked...
example.tran: 这种蔬菜有多种吃法，既可生吃也可烹调后食用。

example.ex: Half of it is burned and half of it is raw.
example.tran: 一半烧焦了，另一半还是生的。

value.def: If a part of your body is raw, it is red and painful, perhaps because the skin has come off or has been burnt.

example.ex: ...the drag of the rope against the raw flesh of my shoulders...
example.tran: 绳子摩擦着我蹭破了皮的肩头

example.ex: Her feet hurt and her hands were rubbed raw from unaccustomed work.
example.tran: 这种活儿她根本做不习惯，双脚疼痛，双手也蹭破了皮。

value.def: Raw emotions are strong basic feelings or responses which are not weakened by other influences.

example.ex: ...the raw passions of nationalism...
example.tran: 朴实的民族主义热情

example.ex: Her grief was still raw and he did not know how to help her.
example.tran: 她仍然沉浸在悲伤中，他不知道如何帮她才好。

value.tran: （情感）不加掩饰的，原始的，朴实的

example.ex: The rawness of his greed was frank and uninhibited.
example.tran: 他的贪婪是赤裸裸的，干脆直接，毫不掩饰。

value.def: If you describe something as raw, you mean that it is simple, powerful, and real.

example.ex: ...the raw power of instinct.
example.tran: 本能的强大力量

example.ex: ...the raw vitality of his earlier painting.
example.tran: 他早期绘画的强大生命力

example.ex: Recorded almost live, there's a certain seductive rawness about the whole thing.
example.tran: 整个作品几乎是实况录制，有一种引人入胜的真实感。

value.def: Raw data is facts or information that has not yet been sorted, analysed, or prepared for use.

example.ex: Analyses were conducted on the raw data.
example.tran: 对原始数据进行了分析。

example.ex: ...a statistical model that fully adjusts the census's raw figures.
example.tran: 全面调整这项普查的原始数据的统计模型

value.def: If you describe someone in a new job as raw, or as a raw recruit, you mean that they lack experience in that job.

example.ex: ...replacing experienced men with raw recruits...
example.tran: 用新手替代有经验的人

example.ex: Davies is still raw but his potential shows.
example.tran: 戴维斯还是新人，但已经显示出了他的潜力。

example.ex: Once they cleared the housetops, the wind was raw and biting.
example.tran: 他们清扫完屋顶后，寒风刺骨。

example.ex: ...a raw December morning.
example.tran: 12月一个阴冷的早上

value.def: Raw sewage is sewage that has not been treated to make it cleaner.

example.ex: ...contamination of bathing water by raw sewage.
example.tran: 洗澡用水被未经处理的污水污染

value.def: If you say that you are getting a raw deal, you mean that you are being treated unfairly.

example.ex: They feel that Quebec is getting a raw deal...
example.tran: 他们觉得魁北克省受到了不公平的待遇。

example.ex: I think women have a raw deal.
example.tran: 我认为妇女受到了不公正的待遇。

value.def: You use in the raw to describe something that is in its true state, and has not been made civilized or respectable.

example.ex: This is nature in the raw...
example.tran: 这是自然的原生态。

example.ex: He also wanted to see Bangladesh in the raw...
example.tran: 他也想看看原生态的孟加拉国是什么样子。

example.ex: It exposes capitalism in the raw.
example.tran: 它暴露了资本主义的本来面目。

value.tran: 未开化的；原生态的；处于蒙昧状态的；原原本本的
